description._content: Original Caption: Religion Plays an Important Part in the Lives of Residents. The Second Largest Denomination of Churchgoers Are Lutherans. the Largest Lutheran Church in Town Is St. Paul's Evangelical Lutheran Church Whose Church Steeple Is Seen in This Photo. The Structure Is Located in the Center of Town. New Ulm Is a County Seat Trading Center of 13,000 Founded in 1854 by a German Immigrant Land Company.
